<p>
  Every reading on a multimeter, clamp meter, insulation tester, or LCR meter traces back to one equation. If you truly understand Ohm's Law, you understand <em>what every electrical tester is actually doing</em> — and why each instrument exists.
</p>

<h2 id="what-is">What Is Ohm's Law?</h2>

<p>
  Stated simply: <strong>the current through a conductor is directly proportional to the voltage across it, and inversely proportional to its resistance</strong>. It was established by German physicist Georg Simon Ohm in 1827 and became one of the bedrock laws of electrical engineering.
</p>

<!-- Formula hero — no dark banner, just the equation centred -->
<div class="my-10 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl bg-[#0D1B2A] text-white overflow-hidden">
  <div class="px-8 py-10 text-center">
    <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[#E0252E] mb-5">The Core Equation</div>
    <div class="text-6xl sm:text-7xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight mb-8" style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;">
      V = I × R
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center gap-10">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#E0252E] mb-1" style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;">V</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] leading-snug">Voltage<br/>(Volts)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-400 mb-1" style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;">I</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] leading-snug">Current<br/>(Amperes)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-1" style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;">R</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] leading-snug">Resistance<br/>(Ohms)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 id="triangle">The OHM Triangle — Rearranging in Seconds</h2>

<p>
  Engineers use a visual triangle to rearrange Ohm's Law on the fly. Cover the quantity you want to find — the remaining two show the calculation.
</p>

<!-- Triangle infographic — light bg, no dark banner -->
<div class="my-8 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl bg-white overflow-hidden">
  <div class="p-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center justify-center">
    <!-- Triangle SVG -->
    <svg viewBox="0 0 200 180" class="w-44 shrink-0" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <polygon points="100,10 10,170 190,170" fill="#0D1B2A" stroke="#E0252E" stroke-width="2"/>
      <line x1="10" y1="110" x2="190" y2="110" stroke="#E0252E" stroke-width="2"/>
      <text x="100" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="38" font-weight="900" fill="#E0252E" font-family="monospace">V</text>
      <text x="63" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="28" font-weight="900" fill="#60A5FA" font-family="monospace">I</text>
      <text x="100" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#94a3b8" font-family="sans-serif">×</text>
      <text x="138" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="28" font-weight="900" fill="#34D399" font-family="monospace">R</text>
    </svg>
    <!-- Three formula cards — light bg, dark text, no CSS conflict -->
    <div class="flex-1 grid gap-3">
      {[
        { cover:'V', result:'V = I × R', desc:'Cover V — multiply current by resistance to find voltage.', border:'border-[#E0252E]', chip:'bg-red-50 text-[#E0252E] border-[#E0252E]' },
        { cover:'I', result:'I = V ÷ R', desc:'Cover I — divide voltage by resistance to find current.', border:'border-blue-400', chip:'bg-blue-50 text-blue-600 border-blue-400' },
        { cover:'R', result:'R = V ÷ I', desc:'Cover R — divide voltage by current to find resistance.', border:'border-emerald-500', chip:'bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 border-emerald-500' },
      ].map(f => (
        <div class={`flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border-2 bg-white ${f.border}`}>
